Code 7 is either code for being out of service (short for 10-7), or a meal break:

http://www.radiolab s.com/police- codes.html
http://www.yougetin fo.com/info/ PolCodes. html


--- On Sun, 5/10/09, Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@ yahoo.com&gt; wrote:


From: Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@ yahoo.com&gt;
Subject: [EVP-ITC] The Seven - interesting tidbit of info
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
Date: Sunday, May 10, 2009, 9:31 PM


Tonight at work I was talking to a state trooper, there had been an accident. I asked him if there were any deaths (it was very very bad) and he said he didnt know so he got on his radio and called in and asked them if it was a 7 at the site. They told him negative, and he told me the little boy who was the worst off was still alive. I asked him why did you ask them if it was a 7. He said code 7, I was asking them if they were dead. So if you ever hear anyone call 7 over the radio that means someones dead.

Just thought I would pass that on. I find it interesting since I know alot of us have heard this before when used to describe who is speaking rather than a name they say seven.

Misty 





      
